content.description: The Jincheng Meteorological 2021 issued a blue gale warning signal at 17:05 on April 14. Affected by the cold air, the city is expected to have the next 24 hours 4 ~ 5 class, a short period of 6 ~ 7 above gale weather. The relevant units and personnel are requested to prepare for windbreaks. Defense Guide: 1. The government and related departments shall do a good job in preventing gale according to their duties. 2. Close doors and windows, reinforce fences, scaffolding, billboards and other wind-sensitive structures, and properly handle outdoor items that are susceptible to high winds and cover construction materials. 3. Pedestrians should ride their bikes as little as possible and don’t stay under billboards, temporary structures, etc. when the wind blows. 4. Relevant departments and units should pay attention to forest and grassland fire prevention.
content.source: National Early Warning Information Release Center
content.title: Blue alert for Gale [ Level IV/general ] issued by Jincheng Meteorological Bureau

content.description: The 2021 of the Jincheng Meteorological Observatory issued a blue frost warning signal at 17:33 on April 14. Due to the impact of cold air, the minimum ground temperature in some villages and towns in Lingchuan County, Gaoping and Qinshui County mountains is expected to fall below 0 °C in the next 48 hours, which will adversely affect agriculture. Please take measures in advance. Defense Guide: 1. The government and the competent departments of Agriculture and forestry shall, in accordance with their duties, prepare for frost prevention. 2. Some protective measures should be taken for crop, vegetable, flower, fruit and forestry breeding. 3. Rural grass-roots organizations and farmers should pay attention to the local frost warning information in order to take measures to strengthen protection.
content.source: National Early Warning Information Release Center
content.title: Jincheng Meteorological Bureau issued Blue Frost Alert [ Level IV/General ]
